<h2>How to sign</h2>
<p>You can sign the petition online at <a href="https://www.change.org/acc4pf" target="_blank">change.org/acc4pf</a>, or in person at petition events throughout the PfISD area. Check back for a schedule of upcoming events.</p>

<h2>Who can sign?</h2>
<p>Any registered voter who lives within PfISD boundaries. This includes residents inside Pflugerville city limits, in the ETJ, and in any area served by Pflugerville ISD.</p>

<h2>What happens after we collect enough signatures?</h2>
<p>The ACC Board of Trustees verifies the petition and calls an election. The vote would be held in November 2026 alongside the general election. Only PfISD-area registered voters vote on the measure. If it passes, in-district benefits begin immediately upon certification.</p>

<h2>What if I have questions first?</h2>
<p>Read the <a href="/faq/">FAQ</a>, check the <a href="/myth-vs-fact/">myth vs. fact page</a>, or <a href="/calculator/">use the calculator</a> to see your specific costs and savings. Then come back and sign.</p>
</div>
